# Student Job Application App - Walkthrough

The application is now set up and running! Here's what you can explore:

## Features

### 1. Home Page
- **Hero Section**: Welcoming interface with a "Browse Jobs" call-to-action.
- **Featured Jobs**: A preview of the latest opportunities.

### 2. Job Listing (`/jobs`)
- **Search**: Type in the search bar to filter by job title or company.
- **Filters**: Click "Internship" or "Full-time" to filter by job type.
- **Job Cards**: Click "View Details" on any job to see more info.

### 3. Job Details (`/jobs/:id`)
- **Full Info**: View salary, location, description, and requirements.
- **Apply Now**: Click the button to open the application modal.
- **Application Form**: Fill out the mock form and submit to see the success message.

### 4. Profile (`/profile`)
- **Student Info**: View the mock student profile (Alex Johnson).
- **Skills & Education**: See the layout for student credentials.

### 5. Saved Jobs (`/saved-jobs`)
- **Save**: Click the heart icon on any job card to save it.
- **View**: See all your saved jobs in one place.

### 6. Company Dashboard (`/dashboard`)
- **Switch Role**: Use the toggle in the navbar to switch to "Company View".
- **Manage Jobs**: View list of posted jobs and their applicant counts.
- **Post Job**: Click "Post a Job" to open the modal and create a new listing.

### 7. Authentication
- **Login/Sign Up**: Create an account or log in to access features.
- **Persistence**: Your data (saved jobs, posted jobs) is now saved to your browser, so it won't disappear when you refresh!

## How to Run
If the server stops, you can restart it with:
```bash
npm run dev
```
Then open the URL shown in the terminal (usually `http://localhost:5173`).
